Toothpaste (1 g) was mixed with distilled water (15 mL) in a measuring cylinder, shaken vigorously for 1 min, placed on the table to measure the height of the foam above the water level (Das et al. 2013). The foaming ability of the toothpaste was determined using the following equation.1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
